          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector consisted of a 13 mm diameter by",
                "1 mm Nal crystal mounted on a 6292 photomultiplier",
                "tube."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A small monitor counter was inserted in the",
                "side of the chamber to count reaction products",
                "produced in the solid angle. This counter consists of",
                "a 13 mm diameter by 2 mm Csl crystal shielded with a",
                "2.5 mu-m aluminium foil and mounted on a 6467",
                "photomultiplier tube."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "U.S.P. grade tank oxygen, guaranteed better than 99 %",
                "pure, was used as a target. To lessen any possibility",
                "of contamination, the gas was flowed through the",
                "chamber at the rate of a few cubic centimeters per",
                "minute. The pressure was set at about 50 mm Hg,",
                "controlled to 1 % with a Manostat pressure regulator,",
                "and measured to better than 1 % with a Wallace and",
                "Tiernan precision mechanical gauge."
              ]
            }
          ],
